column5: I was out fishing for smallmouth this morning with jig/worm combo on 6lb line. I didn't catch any bass but I did land two nice catfish and carp. They put up crazy fights on the light action rod with 6lb test. The big cat took me 30 minutes to land. Excuse my silly facial expressions. It was hard trying to do a selfie and hold up the bigger fish.    .
Sweet deal dude! Ill take that all day
Nice cats we are in the spawn right now but in a few weeks I will get some pictures up from down South.   Art
Nice kitties. Do you eat them?
I let them go. The waters here are pretty contaminated with heavy metals.
I let them go. The waters here are pretty contaminated with heavy metals. That's unfortunate.  Are those flatheads or channels?
Flatheads. We have channel cats and blues too.
